						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Sūryanārāyaṇasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>1490 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14[1]1, Saumya, Mīna 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1490 A.D., February 25.</hi> The details given, however, are not verifiable.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land for offerings to god Sūryanārāyaṇadēva of Nārāvi by Kāmādēvi, mother of <hi rend="italic">Maṇḍalika</hi> Sōmanātha Peṁnnaṁṇṇaarasa.</p>						

						</summary>
